<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4545170>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 55. Dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views of the skull of the holotype of Eptesicus andinus (AMNH 33807; male) from Colombia. Dorsal (C) and ventral (D) views of the skull of E. chiriquinus (AMNH 267234; male) from Paracou. E. chiriquinus has a consistently larger and more heavily built skull than does E. andinus. Also note the flattened, triangular bony plate at the intersection of the sagittal and nuchal crests in andinus, a structure never present in chiriquinus. Scale bars = 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4545170/files/figure.png" .
